						Isaac Fowler and Mary Moore
					

 Jnstock20
(View posts)




					Posted:	997304539000


					Classification: 


						Edited: 1029456062000


					Surnames: 






Caroline - Isaac and Mary went from Laurens Co SC to  Knox Co KY in early 1800's and then went to Schuyler Co IL after 1830. Mary died in 1850 and Isaac went to Jefferson Co KS to live with his son Isaac H.  He died there in 1861.Their children as far as we can determine were1. Sallie (Sarah?) Fowler m. John McMurtry2. Jane Fowler m. William Campbell 25 Aug 1825 in Knox Co KY.3. Deborah Fowler m. Thomas Fowler4. Elizabeth Fowler m. James Pemberton 22 Mar 1827 Knox Co KY5. Rosannah Fowler m. Jesse Langdon6. Mary "Polly" Fowler m. John Weaver 30 Jan 1823 in Knox Co KY. She died in Schuyler Co IL7. Thomas R. Fowler (or may be Thomas "I" and I hope that is true for he was my ggg'father. His middle initial has always been mixed up and we are searching something now that will definitely tie him to Isaac.  Isaac was living with him in IL in 1850 after Mary died and Mary was the daughter of Jesse so it stands to reason that Thomas I. is Isaac's son but we can't prove it yet) As I said, his wife Mary Fowler Fowler was the daughter of Jesse and Deborah.  They went back to KY after Jesse (and maybe Deborah too) died shortly after 1860 and he died there Jan. 9 1865, murdered, they say.  I think I may have the last letter he wrote, which was to his son Jesse in Schuyler Co IL on Jan 1 1865.8. Isaac H. Fowler b. 4 Oct 1806 in KY. Married Margaret Campbell 10 May 1827 Knox Co KY. She was daughter of Jane and William Campbell. They stayed in KY until after 1850 when they left and went to IL and on to Jefferson Co KS where they died and were buried in the Fowler Cemetery.9. William Fowler b. about 1809 in KY. He was handicapped and lived with Isaac H. in KS. Old Isaac made provisions for his lifetime care before he died.10. Alice Fowler m. Jubal DeWees.         We had thought Isaac and Jesse were brothers but now know that Jesse was the son of John Fowler in Laurens Co SC and we are trying to find out the parents and siblings of Isaac, to no avail so far.          Will be glad to hear of anything you have to help me fill in the blanks.  You may write me back direct at stockham @telepath.com    Jean in OK  





















