Hi, I'm Becky Root. I was so glad to see your info. on the ch of Old Isaac. I am from Old Isaac's bro. Wm., both thought to be sons of Joseph. I have been gathering evidence on possible sons of Joseph for 20 years. I will be glad to send to you info. if you want, & can send me your current e-mail. I have some questions:Old Isaac b 1770 m Mary Moore. When you say Isaac was living w/ Thomas in IL in 1850 after Mary died. You mean Mary Moore died 1850?, not Thomas' wife, right? Then is this Thomas’s wife Mary you say was the dau. of Jesse & Deborah Fowler? Are you saying Thomas was in IL in 1850, then went back to Knox Co., KY in 1850? So did Jesse Fowler die in 1850 IL? Who were the ch of Thomas w/ dates & places please? Do you have any dates or places for the births of Old Isaac's ch? Do you have the names, dates & places for the ch. of Jesse?) Was Thomas in IL in 1828 to have a son John? Please write to me at byroot@yahoo.com





















						Re: Isaac Fowler and Mary Moore
					

					Becky Root
					
					(View posts)




					Posted:	1152083534000


					Classification: Query


					Surnames: Fowler, Rowland, Middleton, Mitchell, Henderson, Fleming, Stribling, etc.






A probable bro. of Isaac Fowler b 1770 who m Mary Moore, is John Fowler b 1781 who m Eliz. Moore. I don't know if you are interested in these Moores or not, but they are from the Laurens Dist., SC. The following is from a letter Troy Jones wrote to my mother, Sue Yett, in 1973. Troy Jones was a descendant.John Fowler m2  Eliz. Alexander MOORE, dau of JOHN MOORE and Jane Patton Alexander   of same area. She was 4th of 9 Moore ch. Troy Jones says 3 of the 9 are in the 1790 census. The 9 ch of John Moore are:                                                                                                 1. Martha m Jeremiah Collins to AL, but a grson lived in Greenwood Co.,SC & has a large family. 2. Ann Moore m Thomas Scurlock                                                                             3. Margaret m John Cullen Watkins- 2 sons & 1 dau. They were easily the most prominent family                        of the group. Included are: a Federal Judge, sister m a Miami millionaire, etc.                        4. Eliz. Moore b 1792-1871 m John Fowler b 1781 in probably Greene Co., TN (was Wash. Co., NC).                                                                       5. John King Moore 1796-1851. 1 dau. here (Laurens Co., SC), John King Jr. to Miss., &  Samuel            Asbury Moore to TX.                                                                                                6. Lucinda Moore 1798-1887 m John Henderson (grandmaâ€™s uncle). 7. Jesse Moore b either 1794 or 1800 no record. 8. George Moore 1802- 186_ m Eliz. McDaniel 1808-186_. 10 ch: 1 to TX,     1 to Greenwood Co. & Laurens  Co.,SC. 9. Millicent Emeline bc1805 m Elias Brock, lived near Commerce, GA.                                     John Moore d 1806 & afterwards daus. Margaret & Eliz. postponed m to help their    mother, both m about age 30.                                                                                            John Fowler m2c 1822 Eliz. (Betsy) Alexander Moore & had 5 ch. after the 5 he had with Eliz.                               Pinson. John Fowler & Eliz. (Betsy Moore) ch:  6(6). Wade Alexander b 21 Nov 1823- d. 25 Jan 1897 SC;                                                                 m 14 Jun 1849 Hannah C. HENDERSON,           a niece of  his bro. Wm.â€™s wife. (Troyâ€™s grfather). After grandma, Hannah, died 1883,                  he m2 13 Oct 1884 Louisa Taylor 1838-1912. There were 4 sons & 2 daus. The youngest                                     dau. was my, (Troy Jones),  mother, Josephine Jones.             7-1? Wade Drayton Fowler (Simpsonville, SC) m Manie Jones of Laurens. 2 ch:              8-1. Wade Fowler               8-2. Maude Fowler m Ben F. Keller (Greenville, GA) & had dau. m a Nowlen & had:                                  Paul Nowlen  P O Box 11   Jenkinsville, SC 29065  Paul@hotmail.com                        Paul & Cathi cleaned & photographed the headstones of John & Eliz. Moore Fowler                                                             & also a few feet away, Wade & his wife, all at Mt. Pleasant Baptist Church south of                        Laurens. Paul lives abt. An hour away.            7-2? James Dexter (Uncle Dex) lives Miami, FL barely living in 1935. Has 1 adopted son.            7-3? Alice has cataracts            7-4? Max had a dau. who is almost deaf, as an older person.                                            7-5? son                                                                                                                                                    7-6? Josephine bc 1883?  m Jones, had G. Troy Jones, genealogist, no m.6(7). Wiley Young Fowler b 12 Sep1825 Laurens Dist., SC & d. 15 or 26 Mar1917  Burnet Co.,                                  TX              m 23 Mar 1848 in Parrottsville, Cocke Co., TN to Mary Jane YETT b 8 Nov. 1824              Cocke Co., TN, d. 26 Apr 1912 Burnet Co., TX. Both are buried in the Fowler Cem.                          